cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.PL, cs.DS

This paper is primarily focused on database management systems (DBMS) and their performance on modern multi-core machines. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DB (Database). Additionally, the paper discusses parallelization techniques and runtime analysis, which are relevant to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new mechanism for log recovery, which involves static and dynamic analysis of stored procedures, making it relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of transaction processing, which is relevant to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
